{"word":"ἐπόψιος","slug":"ἐπόψιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπόψιος</b></el> <el>(ἐπόψιος, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὄψις'><el>ὄψις</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>full in view, conspicuous</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>overlooking all things</i>, of gods, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}